column6: "description":"Espresso is a concentrated form of coffee produced by forcing hot water under high pressure through finely-ground coffee beans. Originating in Italy

column6: "description":"White tea may refer to one of several styles of tea which generally feature young or minimally processed leaves of the Camellia sinensis plant. Currently there is no generally accepted definition of white tea and very little international agreement on how it can be defined."

"description":"Green tea is a popular tea variety and is made from the Camellia sinensis plant. It is unoxidised and contains less caffeine than black tea. It is fired or steamed shortly after picking in order to prevent the oxidation process. It often has a fresh flavour profile that can be slightly grassy. Popular varieties of green tea include Sencha

"description":"Ginger ale is a carbonated soft drink flavoured with ginger. It is consumed on its own or used as a mixer
